reviews.text: A nice beach - very aesthetic. There’s usually a lot of people, and actively going on. Sunset time is packed because it’s the west side of the island. The water is clear, the ocean floor is smooth and bare for a long ways out. There’s constantly people building stuff in the sand, and there’s always people paddle boarding by the shore, with boats in the distance.

It's stunning! Giving a 4 because it's too touristy for my taste. But, great beach side places for food and drinks. Very calm and shallow water, fine white sand, cool shaded areas from coconut trees. Can't really ask for more (just less people 😉😆).

Amazing white..ish soft powder like sand. Clear blue waters. Very relaxing beach. During low tide, a sand bar show up. When the tides are in, the water is still calm. Perfect for all ages to enjoy. Best beach I've ever been to!

Still by far one of the Best Beaches in the world!  I just wish people will continue to take care of the island's natural habitat to ensure that future generations can still enjoy the beauty of this island.
We were well handled here, food is great, my Korean spicy dish was superb. They also offered us two vodkas for the price of one. Superb time.
Less crowded side of the island. Beautiful sand and waters. Perfect for picnic.
To get away from the crowds on white beach and experience a great sunset come to this beach
Amazing views, beach was completely empty. Water is clean, but be careful about jellyfishes.
This place is surreal! No words to describe such magical place!
Too far from main beaches and too tough wave
Chicken is great! Place is clean, staff are all attentive to customers.
i like the chicken verry tender and juicy
Love the chicken!!
Ok
Affordable than the others

It was open late hours! Fast food restaurant location is good but food was not so good.I ordered fish and chips.I only are chips than pack the remaining fish and on my way back to my hotel I gave it to the stray dog but smelled it but did not it..
Not polite, no thank you. Waitress so rude. Banana pancakes terrible.
great burgers expensive though
A paradise for fatty food lovers or after parties. Open 24 hours, good prices and tasty food. Located at the D'mall just by the beach.
Had a good Filipino breakfast here. The food was great and satisfying. Nice view of the beach and people walking by. Friendly staff and service.

Loved our breakfast here. It's a great beachfront restaurant to hang out. The prices are good. The fried rice and adobo tasted weird. It's too sour for my taste. If you're craving for pancakes, this is the place for you. The staff is super nice and helpful.

The catering service in this place is very good and very atmospheric. The staff is very polite and provides good service to the customers. We had a five-course meal, and all the food was great! The taste and setting are absolutely first class! Chef Omar visits us to check if everything is ok and if the food is delicious. I admire his skills and passion for food. This gives me and my boyfriend a perfect romantic dinner. We have such a wonderful night, everything is very good in the upper lira. The atmosphere, setting, service and dining are impeccable. Our dinner was part of a very cheap romantic combination, so we envisioned a main course and some others. The restaurant presented us with four exquisite dishes and bread. The staff is excellent and the chef personally talks to all the guests who are dining. This restaurant is highly recommended.
Great selection of salads that you can customize it. Friendly service! Nice outdoors sitting area with view to the beach. Nice spa on site as well for an amazing massage after lunch!

Some people claim this place to serve "the best breakfast in the country", so my hopes were high. Honestly, i've been dreaming about salmon eggs Benedict for quite a time, so had no doubt in choosing what breakfast i want. I also ordered some new coffee specialty. And relaxed happy overlooking the beach.
That's were the dream ended. My first coffee choice was not available and the second was ruined. So if you want coffee here, take something simple, like cappuccino.
The food was nothing better. The eggs Benedict were overcooked, so i had to send back the first try (credit  to the servers they took them back with apologies). They reassembled the dish with new poached eggs, but it couldn't save it. I would still rate it positively, but the inflated prices they have assume another level of quality.

The pancakes were amazing, but the bacon was fatty and the serving sizes were way too big. It seems like breakfast and baked good are the things to order if you go. I had the chicken and it was not great.

This restaurant has 2 separate sides and we only went to the Filipino side where the food is a fraction of the price. It was great food, really authentic, we went back 3 times. Staff are friendly too.

The best restaurant we found in Boracay.  The food was excellent.  We had a delicious white bean soup and shared the seafood paella.  The service was good.  The entertainment was also first rate.  Two  acts alternated - a Spanish style solo guitarist and a man/woman singer/guitarist that played a wide variety of material.  We spent several nights listening to the music and sampling the food.

Every trip to Boracay must include at least one dinner at this restaurant. The ambiance of a Southern Spanish tapas bar with the hospitality that can only be found in the Philippines. From the staff to the musicians to the food, everything was perfect. We felt like part of the family and cannot wait to go back again.

We came half an hour before closing and we were greeted with an eye rolling look, there after the staff pressured us to eat and finsh, The employees constantly laughed and made rude remarks to each other.
Nice food, bit over priced the employees let the place down.
Great atmosphere and good quality food. Just a little aways from the beach. Which makes it an ideal place to get a good meal with a touch of ambience.
Excellent service (Waiter named Erron) and delicious sushi with a large variety. I strongly recommend.
Bad food. Bad servise. High price. Not Japanese food at all. Very disappointed.

I've eaten at Hama twice in the last few months. The sushi is fresh and absolutely terrific. My friend ordered the lunch special which had a variety of sashimi. I did the same but went with the tuna. The bill with tip was $80, which is reasonable given that you're in Manhattan. You'll sit on top of the people next to you, but hey, it's New York, so that's to be expected. This has quickly become a "go to" place for me.

The food is not great and expensive. We ordered Chicken teriyaki (dry and needs more seasoning) & Katsudon with miso soup (nothing special with the katsudon and the miso soup tastes just like miso powder then water).
Food OK. Service non existant. Still waiting for our change in an empty restaurant. Suggestion put a service button on every table. There is more than enough bored staff around.
Great location
Awesome to have this to take picnics to the beach!
Good selection of cheese..

reviews.author_name: อเล็กซานเด สเตฟาน
reviews.text: Единственное место на Боракае где есть приличный выбор импортной (европейской) гастрономии. Большой выбор качественных сыров, колбас, мяса, вина, сладостей, макаронных изделий. Всё отличного качества, напрямую из европейских стран.

This place has a decent beer selection, organized by country of origin. They offer build your own flights, and have a quiet and comfortable atmosphere. Good date spot, if you're looking for something casual.

I like Imperial porters and stouts they had none. 
They only let you taste 2 beers. Not much of a food menu. The place is small, so they put reservation signs on the tables, to make sure the tables are full. I settled for an Einstock porter and wings. Almost all there beers are $9 for different sizes. Wings were decent.
Great craft beer selection! Bright corner view of the avenue. Not really the place to go for food though.

My new favorite bar in the neighborhood. A nice variety of drinks and an excellent atmosphere. Full of people there to have a good time with friends. The service was prompt too, and the bratwurst wasn't bad either. They didn't try and get too fancy with their sauerkraut either, which I appreciate.

I love this place! The atmosphere is great, cozy. Awesome beer selection. The staff are friendly and welcoming for the most part, in particular the super sweet bartender Gail! I highly recommend this cozy spot for a few drinks and some yummy food.
Excellent food.  Lovely atmospheres. Fair prices. Just perfect. I would highly recommend
Restaurant's setting is really pleasant. I found the couscous tasted very good, they could probably be more generous with the portion though.
Really nice place with delicious food and cosy atmosphere. Good tea creme brulee and tajin. Will recomend it.
Very good food, they only need to improve their service.

Pros:
- The staff is very welcoming, good at English and will give you good service. [5/5]
- The food tastes fresh, perfectly cooked and is well seasoned. [4/5]
The atmosphere is warm and looks very pretty. The lighting, colours and furniture is in good harmony and everything feels well thought out. [4.5/5]

Cons:
- None to speak of.

The family portion rice is not for 3 but I think 5~6, very dissatisfied with the waitress. Overall it was terrible service. When we order, there are so many menu not available too. Have to reorder again and again. From all the menu we ordered in the end, only that beef on a steak plate is good. The others are so-so. Don't buy the belly tuna, it's nothing special. The guitarist singer are good tho.
Good taste but expensive compared to other restaurants nearby.
Their ube milkshake is fantastic. Food is also very good.
awesome...great food..tummy full and satisfied...
A bit expensive, but the BBQ ribs were good
Their chicken is good, but I honestly would rather eat at Jollibee and it's cheaper.
Gorgeous dishes on the menu. Good selection for Europeans as well for Asians. Fish and chips are very good and it's a big portion. If you are going to boracay you have to eat there at least one time
Great value and tasty dori burger! Better than any fish burger back in London!
only the dory chips are good. the oyster are bad. no tilapia available during my visit.
This is a Chinese restaurant.the food is not bad
Such a relaxing resort in front of white beach. Recommended for family and Solo travelers too. They have bar and restaurant also with good breakfast opens. Worth for money.
Right on beach front, White Beach

This place is the best if your looking to spend time on the beach all day and have a great dinner in the evening. Staff's are really friendly and will do the extra mile for you to make you feel comfortable. That is why my family and I keep coming back to this resort. It's affordable and the rooms are cozy and well maintained. What more can a vacationing family ask for! Closest to the beach, easy access to all the food joints and it is in the middle of Station 2. Free use of sun  bed and beach towel. We will becoming back to this place very soon.
verry friendly people and nice place
Breakfast was nice. Rooms were small. Air conditioning was limited. Facilities limited. For a budget beach front option, it's pretty good.

I've eaten here 3 times. The first time was amazing. My sister and I ended up ordering 4 entrees lol. The other times were just mediocre. It's good Greek food in the Philippines. I've had better Greek food in NYC.

Excellent Greek food everything is tasty and I have ate her multiple times. The lamb souvlaki was tasty and so was the moussaka was really good. Also I tried the chicken wrap which was good too. Service is good and the place is clean for the right price because quality meats used for everything

Good food. But they don't have clean service water.
You have to buy bottled water or bring your own.
Very tasty food, affordable, quick service! The Greek yogurt and honey desert is simply fantastic!
The burrito, crab pasta, and flaming cheese is awesome.

Love walking into a Starbucks and smelling the fresh coffee. This location was clean and the staff friendly. Coffee was made to order and correctly made for this picky coffee drinker lol. This spot has an area for when you are wanting to socialize or break out the computer/books and do some studying while sipping on a latte. Only problem I seen was the drive through and parking area are very tight but couldn't take a star away just for that. Keep it up at this location cause my little girl and I will definitely be back for our coffee.
Always fast, friendly, and informative! Their coffee is great and their snacks are always yummy! Mobile pickup through their app is always very convenient as well!

Yummy but prices need to stop going up, they  are beyond being a very successful business that has millions of people addicted and stopping for ine of their many yummy beverages and foods almost every day like its crack, stop being greedy with the cost increase of everything, PLEASE. I want to be able to afford my coffee "crack" lol just playing, kinda. Attention there's no illegal drugs served at any Starbucks facility
... that I'm aware of!
Very friendly service. Got the order correct. Fast.
Rude, impersonal staff, slow service, dirty restrooms. The food is blah, you get better quality food at much lower prices at McDonalds or any of the other fast food chains in the area.
